&lt;div class=&quot;content-intro&quot;&gt;&lt;p&gt;Revivn is a profitable and rapidly growing company that helps enterprises manage their technology through our end of life software platform. We take electronic recycling one step further by repurposing hardware that still has remaining life and providing it to people who lack dedicated computer access and make it more affordable for people who may not be able to purchase new technology. Working with companies like Instacart, Lyft, Qualtrics, X, Gensler, and Spotify, we are changing the way companies view used technology with a new model that focuses on repurposing instead of recycling.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;As a Driver at Revivn, you&#39;ll play a critical role in our mission to give new life to old technology. This position is much more than driving—you&#39;re one of the primary faces of Revivn, providing white glove service to our customers while ensuring the secure collection, transportation, and handling of enterprise IT assets.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You&#39;ll operate a 26-foot box truck to complete scheduled pickups throughout the Fresno area and surrounding regions, averaging 7-10 collection trips each week. You&#39;ll regularly interact with building management, security personnel, and client representatives to coordinate pickups, maintain chain of custody, and deliver an exceptional customer experience.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;When you&#39;re not on the road, you&#39;ll support warehouse and facilities operations by receiving and processing incoming hardware, preparing equipment for future pickups, maintaining inventory accuracy, and contributing to the overall efficiency of our operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;This is an in-person position based in Fresno, California. The schedule is Monday through Friday, 7:30am-4:00pm.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Safely operate 26-foot box trucks to transport IT equipment throughout the Fresno area and regional locations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate and execute white glove pickups of enterprise IT equipment from customer offices, data centers, and commercial buildings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a professional representative of Revivn during every customer interaction, demonstrating excellent communication, professionalism, and sound judgment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Load, unload, secure, and transport unboxed electronics and other technology equipment while maintaining chain of custody and protecting customer assets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with inventory tracking, including scanning, documenting, and accurately processing hardware as required.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support facilities operations, including equipment cleaning, hardware processing, and maintaining an organized warehouse.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help maintain inventory accuracy and prepare materials for shipment or customer collection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow all DOT regulations, company safety procedures, and vehicle inspection requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
